    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n4383" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἤτοι</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἦ
            τοι</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">verily, to be sure</span>, particle of
          asseveration (see <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἦ</span>), and antithesis,
          not always to be translated; in correlation <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἤτοι.. αὐτάρ</span> differs from <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μὲν..
            δέ</span> only in so far as disyllabic and initial words must
          necessarily have more weight than monosyllabic and postpositive ones.
          As <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αὐτάρ</span>, q. v., often correlates to
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μέν</span>, so <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἤτοι</span> may be followed by <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δέ</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.68</span></i>, and often.
          Freq. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλλ᾽ ἤτοι</span>, also <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἤτοι μέν,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 1.140</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            211</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 16.451</span></i>. 
        </div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
